## Testing plan

Gates: `build`, `unit-tests`, `constructor-unit-tests` (all three).

- `build` gate: `dotnet build Berreman.slnx -c Release` MUST pass with the four new Optimization files compiling.
- `constructor-unit-tests` gate: runs `OpticalConstructor.Tests`; the new `LocalRefinementTests.fs` MUST pass and increase the count over slice 009's baseline.
  - AC-G3 (LocalRefinementTests): run a [Core] local-refinement on a target/merit set with a lower-bounded thickness of 0; assert the returned refined `OpticalSystem` contains no negative `Thickness` and satisfies each `Inequality` target's hinge to zero within tolerance.
  - AC-G4 (LocalRefinementTests): load measured R/T or Ψ,Δ CSV data and run inverse fitting; assert the resulting `FitTarget` sample points are stored in meters via `WaveLength.value`, and the fit reduces χ² below its initial value.
- `unit-tests` gate: `BerremanTests` stays green (this slice does not touch `BerremanTests`; the full-path Wolfram/needle/bounded tests are slice 011).

## Risks

- **Medium.** The merit residual MUST be assembled from the SAME `Solution.func` evaluator the charts use, so fit and chart never diverge — wiring a parallel evaluator here is the load-bearing mistake. §G.6 MUST share Part F §F.5 `psiDelta` rather than re-deriving Ψ/Δ; forking it splits two definitions of the same quantity. The [Core]/[Standard] tier labels (G.4/G.5 Core, G.6/G.7 Standard) MUST be preserved. §G.5 must not spawn a thread (cancellation is G.10/J.10). Bounded-parameter handling (lower bound 0 for thickness) MUST come from the §G.3 `ParameterBounds`, not a separate validator.

## Hand-off

The fitting core exists and is unit-tested: the [Core] merit/target model (`MeritFunction.fs`) assembling a weighted-LSQ residual through `Solution.func`, the [Core] local-refinement entry point (`LocalRefinement.fs`) with LM default and folding the solution back through the §G.3 mapping, the [Standard] Ψ/Δ ellipsometric targets (`Ellipsometry.fs`, sharing §F.5 `psiDelta`), and [Standard] inverse fitting from measured CSV/tab data (`InverseFit.fs`). Slice 011 adds fit-quality reporting, needle/tunnelling synthesis and global optimization, the Synthesis/Fit operator page, and the Wolfram-reference validation in `BerremanTests/OptimizationTests.fs`. Emit the state-of-the-world file with all required ATX headings (`Where we are`, `What's working`, `Tests`, `Architecture`, `Deferred`, `Gotchas`, `Changelog`) and a fenced `gates:` YAML baseline block carrying the updated `constructor-unit-tests` count so the next slice's `count_at_least` gate has a baseline.
